%% Data Flow Diagram for llama-stack-provider-trustyai-garak
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6

sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as Client
    participant LS as Llama Stack Server<br/>8321/TCP HTTP
    participant Garak as Garak CLI<br/>(subprocess)
    participant Shield as SimpleShieldOrchestrator<br/>(in-process)
    participant vLLM as vLLM Server<br/>HTTP/HTTPS
    participant Safety as Safety API<br/>8321/TCP
    participant Files as Files API<br/>8321/TCP
    participant KFP as Kubeflow Pipelines<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant S3 as S3/MinIO<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    Note over Client,S3: Flow 1: Inline Garak Security Scan
    Client->>LS: POST /v1/eval/run<br/>No Auth
    LS->>Garak: Spawn subprocess<br/>(semaphore-controlled)
    Garak->>vLLM: POST /openai/v1/chat/completions<br/>API Token (Bearer)
    vLLM-->>Garak: LLM Response
    Garak-->>LS: Scan results (JSON, HTML, hitlog)
    LS->>Files: Upload reports via Files API
    Client->>LS: GET /v1/eval/jobs/status
    LS-->>Client: Job status
    Client->>LS: GET /v1/eval/jobs/result
    LS-->>Client: Scan results + file IDs

    Note over Client,S3: Flow 2: Shield-Integrated Scan
    Client->>LS: POST /v1/eval/run<br/>(with shields config)
    LS->>Garak: Spawn subprocess
    Garak->>Shield: Function-based generator call
    Shield->>Safety: POST /safety/run-shield<br/>(Input Shield - Prompt-Guard-86M)
    Safety-->>Shield: Shield result (pass/block)
    Shield->>vLLM: POST /openai/v1/chat/completions<br/>API Token
    vLLM-->>Shield: LLM Response
    Shield->>Safety: POST /safety/run-shield<br/>(Output Shield - Llama-Guard-3-8B)
    Safety-->>Shield: Shield result (pass/block)
    Shield-->>Garak: Shielded response

    Note over Client,S3: Flow 3: Remote KFP Execution
    Client->>LS: POST /v1/eval/run<br/>(remote mode)
    LS->>KFP: Submit pipeline run<br/>HTTPS/TLS, Bearer Token
    KFP-->>LS: Pipeline run ID
    Note over KFP: Step 1: validate_inputs
    Note over KFP,vLLM: Step 2: garak_scan (GPU/CPU)
    KFP->>vLLM: Vulnerability probes<br/>API Token
    vLLM-->>KFP: LLM Responses
    KFP->>Files: Upload scan reports
    Note over KFP,S3: Step 3: parse_results
    KFP->>S3: Upload artifacts<br/>AWS IAM credentials
    LS->>S3: Retrieve results<br/>AWS IAM credentials
    S3-->>LS: Scan artifacts
    Client->>LS: GET /v1/eval/jobs/result
    LS-->>Client: Results with vulnerability scores (0.0-1.0)
